<subSubSection id="71CB6556FFCFFFDFFF34DA7BB8B7FD22" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="396E36DDFFCFFFDFFF34DA7BB8B7FD22" blockId="3.[151,1436,530,771]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="0BA5EACFFFCFFFDFFF34DA7BB907FDD6" bold="true" box="[199,321,566,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species (wingspan 
<quantity id="FE299B38FFCFFFDFFDA0DA7BBADBFDD6" box="[595,669,566,591]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="15.0">15mm</quantity>
) is distinguished by dentate blackish subtermen on whitish fore- and hindwings. The male abdomen and genitalia can be distinguished by the short claw-like left and long, medially bent right cerata on the eighth sternite, the long digitate socii, and the short, distally tapered fibula and thumb-like valvula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="71CB6556FFCFFFDFFF34DA8BBC43FD46" box="[199,1029,710,735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="134" type="biology_ecology">
